			  	I agree with both posts above.<br />
<br />
Think DarkRaptor's idea would be much easier to implement tho. As mentioned in the manual, massing small ships could be a tactic against big ships. However, now it isn't possible because of the ship limit per commander and the fleet limit per battle.<br />
<br />
That's why doomstars are all that anyone builds once u are able to. Who cares that the encyclopedia says that a doom requires a whole complement of smaller ships to protect it. The small ships cannot hurt a doom simply because it is impossible to bring in enough of them. Small ships have the disadvantage that they die easily = reduced firepower per fleet.<br />
<br />
Maybe make it such that one fleet of dooms could be taken out by say... 10 or so fleets of gunboats? Maybe more. Or make fleet &quot;Mobility&quot; more significant in a battle. That might make small ships more viable and worth building.			   <P align=right></P>
